{{Infobox holiday |holiday_name = International Day of No Prostitution |type = international |image = |imagesize = |caption = |official_name = |nickname = |observedby = [[Feminist views on prostitution|Anti-prostitution feminists]] |litcolor = |longtype = |significance = |begins = |ends = |scheduling = same day each year |date = October 5 |frequency = annual |duration = 1 day |celebrations = |observances = |relatedto = }} {{NPOV|date=October 2015}} '''International Day of No Prostitution''' ('''IDNP''') is an [[awareness day]] that was first observed in 2002. Locations at which IDNP was observed in its inaugural year included the [[San Francisco Bay Area]] of [[California]], United States<ref>{{Cite news|work=Davao Today|title=No Prostitution Day in Davao on October 5|date=September 30, 2008|url=http://davaotoday.com/main/2008/09/30/no-prostitution-day-in-davao-on-october-5/|accessdate=July 26, 2013}}</ref> and [[Melbourne]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], Australia.<ref>{{Cite web|publisher=Women's Health Action|title=Talking about prostitution|date=December 2002|url=http://www.womens-health.org.nz/talking-about-prostitution.html|accessdate=July 26, 2013}}</ref> The day is celebrated annually on October 5 as a manner of opposing [[prostitution]].<ref>{{Cite web|publisher=Alliance of Progressive Labor|title=Survivors challenge legislators on International Day of No Prostitution|date=October 5, 2004|url=http://www.apl.org.ph/ps/2004/20041005catw-ap.htm|accessdate=July 26, 2013}}</ref> In 2005, the [[University of the Philippines]] Institute of Human Rights and the [[Asia-Pacific]] chapter of the [[Coalition Against Trafficking in Women]] (CATW) organized an IDNP event at which they discussed the [[Anti-Trafficking in Persons Act of 2003]].<ref>{{Cite news|work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|title=Sex worker joins campaign vs prostitution|date=October 17, 2005|page=A6}}</ref> In 2008, there was an IDNP [[candlelight vigil]] in [[Phoenix, Arizona|Phoenix]], [[Arizona]].<ref>{{Cite news|work=East Valley Living|title=Plays and Candle Light Walk Part of Prostitution Awareness Week|date=September 15, 2008|url=http://www.evliving.com/2008/09/15/prostitution-awareness-week/|accessdate=July 26, 2013}}</ref> The vigil took place again in 2010, and city leaders and former prostitutes were among the participants.<ref>{{Cite news|work=[[American Broadcasting Company]]|title=Dignity candlelight walk raises awareness about Valley prostitution|author=Jennifer Parks|date=October 9, 2010|url=http://www.abc15.com/dpp/news/region_phoenix_metro/central_phoenix/dignity-candlelight-walk-raises-awareness-about-prostitution-problem|accessdate=July 26, 2013}}</ref> In 2010, CATW observed IDNP by opposing the decision in ''[[Bedford v. Canada]]'' to strike down [[Prostitution law in Canada|Canada's anti-prostitution laws]].<ref>{{Cite web|publisher=[[Coalition Against Trafficking in Women]]|title=Ontario To Traffickers: We're Open For Business|author=Norma Ramos|date=October 19, 2010|url=http://www.catwinternational.org/Home/Article/118-ontario-to-traffickers-were-open-for-business|accessdate=July 26, 2013}}</ref> A group of former [[human trafficking]] victims and [[sex worker]]s in Canada also opposed the striking down of these laws; they [[Picketing (protest)|picketed]] a [[courthouse]] in downtown Toronto, [[Ontario]] in recognition of IDNP. Picketers included [[Natasha Falle]], [[Trisha Baptie]], [[Bridget Perrier]], Katarina MacLeod, and Christine Barkhouse.<ref>{{Cite news|work=[[The London Free Press]]|author=Kevin Connor|title=Former prostitutes picket trade|date=October 6, 2010|url=http://www.lfpress.com/news/canada/2010/10/06/15598191.html|accessdate=June 6, 2013}}</ref> In 2011, People Working Against Prostitution, an organization in the [[Philippines]], expressed their disappointment that the [[Cagayan de Oro]] [[city council]] did not host any events in recognition of IDNP.<ref>{{Cite news|work=[[Sun.Star]]|title=Women group to hold 'fun run'|date=October 4, 2011|url=http://www.sunstar.com.ph/cagayan-de-oro/local-news/2011/10/04/women-group-hold-fun-run-183017|accessdate=July 26, 2013}}</ref>
